<br>
Chaining pets is a good alternative, and more mana efficient.<br>
<br>
1. Don't pull with malaise.  South Karana is so open, just pick a spot and manuver yourself around to avoid adds.<br>
<br>
2. Don't nuke til it runs, and even then use shock of fire just to get the xp.<br>
<br>
3. Chain the Earth/Air/Fire pet on the mob, then med.  1 pet for a Centaur Foul, 2 pets should take a Centaur Archer.  Chargers and Coursers are probably yellow or red, so watch for them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Your Method: 750 total mana</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Pull with Malaise - 60m<br>
3 shock of spikes - 330m<br>
3(?) renew summoning heals - 300m<br>
1 Shield of Flame (just guessing) - 60m<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Pet Chaining: 430 total mana</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1 extra pet - 240m<br>
1 shock of flame - 70m<br>
2 Shield of Flame - 120m<br>
<br>
<br>
