<br>
Sitting aggro can be a very valuable tool. I've been able to occupy the attention of adds (that were snared) by pulling them away from the group with sitting, then standing before they hit me so they try to go back to the snarer, but before they reach the group I sit again ping ponging the adds so that they hit no one at all. Great way to aggro kite with a pet too when those extra seconds of pet health are crucial.<br>
<br>
While chaincasting pets may not be easy at low levels it is still a viable tactic when you have at least one other person to help distract the mob. When you reach the point that pet cost is about equal to a nuke or two, it's a good time to start to consider whether chain casting pets may be more beneficial. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/naladini/pills.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 899<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/03 5:13:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Battle tactics</span><hr size=1> Just one more note for the firepet bandwagon. Make sure to pick up your SolRo focus items. Without the Torch of Alna, the firepet was pretty much worthless. With the torch, hp and ac get boosted and it becomes a very viable pet.<br>
